t Parks & Recreation for premium care. This facility features heated areas for cooler winters, caring and attentive team members, offering pet...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"High Point\",\"addressRegion\":\"NC\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"},\"image\":\"/images/parks/northcarolina/high-point-parks-recreation/high-point-parks-recreation-1.jpg\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I find a dog park in High Point?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Hedgecock Dog Park is the primary off-leash facility, featuring two acres of play space. A permit is required from the Parks & Rec department.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are there dog-friendly trails in High Point?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, the High Point Greenway system offers outstanding paved trails. The Piedmont Environmental Center also has miles of natural surface trails for leashed hikes.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the leash laws in High Point?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"High Point enforces a strict leash law. Dogs must be on a leash and under control when off the owner’s property. There are no exceptions for voice control in public parks.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is High Point University dog-friendly?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The campus is private and generally restricted, but the surrounding greenways and public city parks are very welcoming to pets.\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Dog Parks Directory\",\"item\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\"}